      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are identifying the core tension point for small, budget-sensitive businesses facing wage increases. When you raise prices, you risk alienating customers who are already price-sensitive, potentially driving them toward larger, more scalable competitors. Essentially, the policy creates a difficult trade-off between upholding labor fairness and maintaining price competitiveness in a tight local market. Many small business owners navigate this by focusing on customer loyalty and offering unique value that big box stores cannot match, mitigating the impact of necessary price adjustments.",
